title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 §§ 1627-4.11 - Enforcement
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 §§ 1627-4.11 - Enforcement

State Regulations

The effectiveness of the rules and regulations of
tenancy depends on their impartial enforcement. Prompt handling of infractions
is essential; persons concerned should realize that the authority will not
tolerate any disregard for personal and property rights of other tenants or the
authority. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9
§§
1627-4.11

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
